A woman is in a critical condition after falling 30 metres from the highest lookout in Blue Mountains when she slipped trying to retrieve her mobile phone .
The 44-year-old , slipped and fell from Hassans Fall lookout at Lithgow on Tuesday afternoon .
She was bushwalking with a male friend and her two children , aged 12 and 13 , when she dropped her phone at the lookout , almost 1,100 metres above sea level .
She is believed to have suffered serious head , spinal and chest injuries